==Introduction==
The '''Number Property Type''' represents a numerical values.

The Wiki Automation Tool supports editing, viewing and searching on the Number properties.


==Definition==

The Number Property extends a common definition of the [[Help:Property|Property Definition]] with the following elements:

<pre>
<property ... size={SIZE}>
</property>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {SIZE}
| A length of the input field. Default value: 8.
|}


==Semantic database==
The Number Property is implemented as a [[Special:Types/Number]] MediaWiki datatype.


==Example==
<pre>
<property name="Size" type="Number" label="Size" attribute="size" size="3">
  <description>An integer value used to manage the size of an object in width or height dimensions or other discriminating number.</description>
  <instruction/>
</property>
</pre>


==User Interface==
* '''View Page'''
The property displays a numeric value.

* '''Edit Page'''
The property provides one line text input field to enter numerical value.
A length of the field is controlled by the 'size' attribute.

* '''Search Page'''
The property allows user to choose a search operator from the following options: ''Equals, Less than, Greater than, Has any value''
and allows user to enter a desired numeric value in one line text input field.
